                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/2121: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-13T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 13, 1934—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. Your 27, February 16, 2 p.m. Please ascertain informally from Mello Franco
                    his views as to any progress made in Leticia discussions. What does he foresee
                    as the probable situation next June when the League Commission’s mandate
                    expires? Please inquire informally and confidentially the views of the Brazilian
                    Foreign Office on this last point.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
